Q1. 🧩 1️⃣ What is a Palindrome?
👉 A palindrome is a word, number, phrase, or sequence of characters that reads the same forward and backward.
Example :
| Input                           | Palindrome or Not                   |
| ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- | 
| `"madam"`                       | ✅ Yes                              |
| `"racecar"`                     | ✅ Yes                              |
| `"hello"`                       | ❌ No                               |
| `"121"`                         | ✅ Yes                              |
| `"A man a plan a canal Panama"` | ✅ Yes (if we ignore spaces & case) |

⚙️ Steps to Check Palindrome in Java :
Step 1️⃣
    - Take an input string. like, String str = "madam";
Step 2️⃣
    - Convert the string to a char array (optional)    
    - or use indexes to compare characters directly.
Step 3️⃣
Use two pointers:
    - i → start (0)
    - j → end (length - 1)
Compare characters:
    - if at any point they differ → not palindrome
    - otherwise keep moving inward (i++, j--)
Step 4️⃣
    - If all characters matched → it’s a palindrome ✅
5️⃣ Version That Ignores Case & Spaces (for sentences) :
str = str.replaceAll("\\s+", "").toLowerCase(); // remove spaces & lowercase


